            "id": "c030c6c1656a4fdea66e7",
            "questionText": "A crane lifts a $!$500 kg$!$ steel beam vertically upwards. Initially, the beam is at rest on the ground. The crane exerts an upward tension force, $!$T$!$, through a cable. As the beam ascends, it experiences its weight, $!$W$!$, due to gravity and a drag force, $!$F_d$!$, from the wind opposing its motion. The drag force is proportional to the square of the beam's velocity, given by $!$F_d = bv^2$!$, where $!$b = 2.0 kg/m$!$.\n\nAt a certain height, the crane operator adjusts the tension such that the beam moves upwards at a constant velocity. Calculate the tension $!$T$!$ in the cable when the beam reaches a constant velocity of $!$5 m/s$!$. (Assume $!$g = 9.8 m/s^2$!$)",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "69a8353477054429aaa4d",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by recalling how to calculate the weight of the beam. Identify the correct formula to compute weight from mass and gravitational acceleration.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "ef8aedcd-2a10-45df-a29f-ed2362df9af7"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$W = mg$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$W = m + g$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$W = m/g$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "b63392b393824dc3b9fe0",
                    "stepText": "Now, calculate the beam's weight using the provided mass $!$500 kg$!$ and gravitational acceleration $!$9.8 m/s^2$!$. Plug the values into the formula you selected in the previous step.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "4900"
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "N",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "ef8aedcd-2a10-45df-a29f-ed2362df9af7"
                    ],
                    "options": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "3d8e3adac0714d6090ddb",
                    "stepText": "Next, let's determine the drag force acting on the beam. Identify which formula correctly represents the drag force given that it is proportional to the square of the velocity.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "7a969809-71da-49a4-9e6b-736f7621d7a5"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$F_d = bv^2$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$F_d = b/v^2$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$F_d = bv$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "e3fa9ab2eb5c4d3c95fa7",
                    "stepText": "Now, compute the magnitude of the drag force using $!$b = 2.0\\,kg/m$!$ and velocity $!$v = 5\\,m/s$!$ based on the formula you identified.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "50"
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "N",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "7a969809-71da-49a4-9e6b-736f7621d7a5"
                    ],
                    "options": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "258d7b5a4bef4537a160f",
                    "stepText": "At constant velocity, the beam is in equilibrium. Which relationship correctly represents the balance of forces acting on the beam under these conditions?",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
